(Lee Je Hoon)

2
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:20,550
(Kim Dae Myeong)

3
00:00:21,590 --> 00:00:22,849
(Sung Dong Il)

4
00:00:22,850 --> 00:00:23,989
(Jang Hyun Sung)

5
00:00:23,990 --> 00:00:25,090
(Oh Man Seok)

6
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:27,660
(Ahn Hyun Ho)

7
00:00:28,830 --> 00:00:30,060
(Cha Kang Yoon)

8
00:00:39,870 --> 00:00:43,710
(The Art of Negotiation)

9
00:00:51,910 --> 00:00:53,110
What happened?

10
00:00:53,680 --> 00:00:55,679
There was a withdrawal of
100,000 dollars 2 days ago.

11
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:56,990
But they weren't accounted for.

12
00:00:57,550 --> 00:00:59,320
- In cash? - Yes.

13
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:04,630
Withdrawals must be approved
by CEO Lee Hyeong Taek, right?

14
00:01:05,060 --> 00:01:08,000
Yes. And there is one more
person who can approve of it.

15
00:01:17,110 --> 00:01:18,670
There could be a reason behind that.

16
00:01:18,940 --> 00:01:20,480
Or it could be a mistake.

17
00:01:22,740 --> 00:01:25,450
We don't even know who
made the withdrawal yet.

18
00:01:52,010 --> 00:01:53,010
Bon Joo!

19
00:01:54,110 --> 00:01:55,180
What are you doing here?

20
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:58,110
You took a day off. You
didn't go away or something?

21
00:01:59,380 --> 00:02:01,820
No. Did you come out for lunch?

22
00:02:02,020 --> 00:02:04,020
Yes. I'm sick of eating in the cafeteria.

23
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:06,890
Okay. See you tomorrow.

24
00:02:07,420 --> 00:02:08,460
Okay.

25
00:02:09,860 --> 00:02:11,560
Bye. Watch out for the car.

26
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:32,680
I'll meet with Bon Joo first.

27
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,800
Hello.

28
00:02:52,170 --> 00:02:53,599
Hello.

29
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:55,240
- I'm sorry to bother you. - Hello.

30
00:02:55,670 --> 00:02:57,370
Is Ms. Jeong Bon Joo here?

31
00:02:57,710 --> 00:02:58,940
Bon Joo?

32
00:03:00,540 --> 00:03:02,040
She took a day off today.

33
00:03:03,110 --> 00:03:05,410
But I ran into her at the bank.

34
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:09,420
At the bank? Which bank?

35
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:19,990
Sir.

36
00:03:21,230 --> 00:03:23,570
Hello. What's this about?

37
00:03:25,670 --> 00:03:27,300
You must be on your way out.

38
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:30,070
Yes. Why do you ask?

39
00:03:31,370 --> 00:03:32,670
I need to talk to you.

40
00:03:33,210 --> 00:03:34,910
Could you spare me a moment of your time?

41
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:37,610
I need to get going now.

42
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:39,450
What's this about?

43
00:03:39,950 --> 00:03:41,119
I'm here to make a withdrawal.

44
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:43,180
- How much? - All of it.

45
00:03:46,790 --> 00:03:48,420
Ms. Jeong Bon Joo?

46
00:03:48,890 --> 00:03:49,890
Yes.

47
00:03:49,891 --> 00:03:52,190
You want to withdraw everything in cash?

48
00:03:53,330 --> 00:03:54,330
Yes.

49
00:03:54,930 --> 00:03:56,660
Why? Is it not possible?

50
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:59,100
No. Hold on.

51
00:04:02,340 --> 00:04:03,340
What?

52
00:04:05,270 --> 00:04:08,080
Mr. Yoon. Don't you think
you're being unreasonable now?

53
00:04:09,340 --> 00:04:11,150
How could you after
conducting due diligence?

54
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:15,320
You know how hard I worked
for GREEN VIEW Country Club.

55
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:18,590
Are you suspecting me?

56
00:04:19,290 --> 00:04:21,060
I understand your frustration.

57
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:24,090
But you're authorized to make withdrawals.

58
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:31,530
So how much are we missing?

59
00:04:33,300 --> 00:04:34,770
We're missing 100,000 dollars.

60
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:36,070
What?

61
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:37,940
Did you say 100,000 dollars?

62
00:06:17,870 --> 00:06:22,480
(Episode 10: Loyalty)

63
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:33,590
(Conference Room)

64
00:06:51,170 --> 00:06:52,240
If...

65
00:06:52,910 --> 00:06:54,279
embezzlement is confirmed,

66
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:56,010
we must notify the Audit Team first.

67
00:06:56,710 --> 00:06:58,780
After the Audit Team
investigates this matter,

68
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:01,880
they will decide whether or
not they will file criminal charges.

69
00:07:02,220 --> 00:07:04,250
Let's find Ms. Jeong Bon Joo first.

70
00:07:04,790 --> 00:07:06,790
Nothing has been confirmed yet.

71
00:07:06,850 --> 00:07:08,889
If you're saying so for my sake...

72
00:07:08,890 --> 00:07:12,030
Selling GREEN VIEW
Country Club is our top priority.

73
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:15,360
To do that, it's more important to
find the missing 100,000 dollars.

74
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:18,500
What if we find her and get the money back?

75
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:20,200
Can it go away as if it never happened?

76
00:07:22,300 --> 00:07:23,810
It can't go away...

77
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:25,910
that easily.

78
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,280
I see.

79
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:32,450
Then I'll come back after I
meet up with some friends.

80
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,630
You know, don't you?

81
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,530
That's what everyone is talking about.

82
00:08:25,030 --> 00:08:26,630
Everyone is utterly shocked.

83
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:31,639
We must find Bon Joo quickly,
so she can return the money.

84
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:33,410
Or this could be really bad for her.

85
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,210
Will she go to prison?

86
00:08:37,780 --> 00:08:40,279
The punishment for
embezzlement is getting harsher.

87
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:41,380
So that's a possibility.

88
00:08:43,580 --> 00:08:45,890
But we really don't know anything.

89
00:08:47,190 --> 00:08:48,819
You know what she is like.

90
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:50,490
Bon Joo isn't the type
to discuss this openly.

91
00:08:56,130 --> 00:08:57,130
Jung Hwa.

92
00:08:58,830 --> 00:08:59,930
You don't know anything?

93
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,000
No.

94
00:09:10,710 --> 00:09:14,150
If we find her quickly, I can help her.

95
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:15,950
Give me a call.

96
00:09:17,090 --> 00:09:19,950
I'll call you the moment I
get any news about her.

97
00:09:20,990 --> 00:09:22,020
Okay.

98
00:09:22,460 --> 00:09:23,490
Bye.

99
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:26,360
- Don't skip your meal. - Okay.

100
00:09:55,260 --> 00:09:56,320
Hey, Jung Hwa.

101
00:09:56,690 --> 00:09:58,090
Are you on your way to Seoul now?

102
00:09:58,230 --> 00:10:00,230
No, I'm at the terminal now.

103
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,900
I just wanted to wish you a safe trip.

104
00:10:07,030 --> 00:10:08,100
By the way,

105
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:10,640
would you be interested in seeing Moon Jin?

106
00:10:11,210 --> 00:10:12,340
Moon Jin? Why?

107
00:10:13,610 --> 00:10:14,640
You know,

108
00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:17,310
Moon Jin is Bon Joo's closest friend.

109
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:21,650
She's taking a break now, right?

110
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:23,520
Yes.

111
00:10:25,420 --> 00:10:27,190
Is she staying at home?

112
00:10:27,790 --> 00:10:30,020
She's probably in the hospital now.

113
00:10:57,690 --> 00:10:58,720
Moon Jin.

114
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:02,720
Soon Young?

115
00:11:12,770 --> 00:11:14,770
I hope your arm is recovering well.

116
00:11:15,170 --> 00:11:16,200
Yes.

117
00:11:16,340 --> 00:11:18,410
I'll be fine once I have
one more surgery tomorrow.

118
00:11:20,110 --> 00:11:21,440
How did you get injured?

119
00:11:21,980 --> 00:11:23,040
At work.

120
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:26,480
Bon Joo told me that you
were working as a caddie.

121
00:11:26,780 --> 00:11:29,050
Bon Joo? Did you see Bon Joo?

122
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:30,320
Yes.

123
00:11:30,450 --> 00:11:32,850
We grabbed drinks
together. It had been a while.

124
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:34,660
Gosh, it brought back old memories.

125
00:11:35,020 --> 00:11:36,460
I bet it did for you.

126
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,760
- You've been away for some time. - Right.

127
00:11:39,590 --> 00:11:42,430
- Oh, yes. When did you see Bon Joo?
- Yesterday.

128
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,129
- Yesterday? - Yes.

129
00:11:44,130 --> 00:11:45,770
- I see. - She visits me often.

130
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:48,470
It might be because she feels bad.

131
00:11:49,170 --> 00:11:51,170
It's not like I got injured because of her.

132
00:11:52,940 --> 00:11:55,380
My arm was injured
because the cart tipped over.

133
00:11:57,140 --> 00:11:58,850
- The golf cart? - Yes.

134
00:12:05,950 --> 00:12:08,920
But our customers were also
in the cart when it tipped over.

135
00:12:09,420 --> 00:12:11,690
Other customers were badly injured too.

136
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,200
How bad were the injuries?

137
00:12:15,830 --> 00:12:16,830
Well,

138
00:12:17,470 --> 00:12:19,430
they didn't have bone fractures like I did.

139
00:12:19,900 --> 00:12:21,700
But there was a severe injury to the face.

140
00:12:23,540 --> 00:12:24,840
They even filed a lawsuit against me.

141
00:12:25,340 --> 00:12:26,340
Really?

142
00:12:27,010 --> 00:12:28,210
Were you able to settle?

143
00:12:28,780 --> 00:12:30,410
Yes. They said they would be lenient.

144
00:12:33,050 --> 00:12:34,050
I see.

145
00:12:35,180 --> 00:12:36,680
Bon Joo took care of it.

146
00:12:37,490 --> 00:12:38,720
She's the best.

147
00:12:39,350 --> 00:12:40,420
Isn't she so cool?

148
00:12:41,590 --> 00:12:42,590
Yes.

149
00:12:42,591 --> 00:12:44,990
She was the one who
suggested this position.

150
00:12:45,730 --> 00:12:48,100
She said I could make good
money if I was a good caddie.

151
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:49,729
I see.

152
00:12:49,730 --> 00:12:52,070
- That's how you started it. - Yes.

153
00:12:53,430 --> 00:12:55,100
At first, I turned it down...

154
00:12:55,740 --> 00:12:57,339
because I'd get the job
based on her recommendation.

155
00:12:57,340 --> 00:12:59,610
But if I didn't do a good job,
it would affect her reputation.

156
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:02,340
But she said she had already paid.

157
00:13:04,050 --> 00:13:05,080
Pay for what?

158
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:07,849
To become a caddie, you
need to go through training.

159
00:13:07,850 --> 00:13:09,920
But before that, you must put
down 300 dollars as a deposit.

160
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:12,450
She also paid for that.

161
00:13:14,190 --> 00:13:17,120
But she still felt
responsible for the accident.

162
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:25,929
By the way, Bon Joo went to
the injured customer and begged.

163
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:27,640
The customer who demanded
100,000 dollars initially...

164
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:28,970
decided to just settle.

165
00:13:31,510 --> 00:13:32,840
- Is that what she said? - Yes.

166
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:34,980
But I know that's a lie.

167
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:37,410
I doubt she begged them to settle.

168
00:13:37,610 --> 00:13:38,910
She probably made a scene.

169
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:41,580
You know what Bon Joo is like.

170
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:44,750
I do.

171
00:14:05,540 --> 00:14:07,209
It might seem Bon Joo
is always confident...

172
00:14:07,210 --> 00:14:09,780
and doesn't care about what people think.

173
00:14:10,310 --> 00:14:11,909
But she's so sensitive...

174
00:14:11,910 --> 00:14:13,880
when it comes to inconveniencing others.

175
00:14:14,850 --> 00:14:16,620
She's generous about other people's flaws.

176
00:14:16,780 --> 00:14:18,890
But she's so strict about her flaws.

177
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:25,260
Hello.

178
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:28,300
I'm Jeong Bon Joo from
GREEN VIEW Country Club.

179
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:31,130
How can I get a meeting with
the manager of M and A Team?

180
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:33,500
- What was your name again?
- It's Jeong Bon Joo.

181
00:14:38,010 --> 00:14:39,040
Yes.

182
00:14:42,110 --> 00:14:43,210
Yes, thank you.

183
00:14:46,350 --> 00:14:48,680
Ms. Jeong is in the lobby now.

184
00:14:58,560 --> 00:14:59,560
Hello.

185
00:15:04,430 --> 00:15:05,530
You should go.

186
00:15:06,300 --> 00:15:08,770
Well, the thing is...

187
00:15:12,310 --> 00:15:13,670
- Moon Jin. - Yes?

188
00:15:15,980 --> 00:15:16,980
The truth is...

189
00:15:21,250 --> 00:15:22,320
- Hold on. - Okay.

190
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:25,890
- Jin Soo. - Attorney Oh.

191
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:29,290
Ms. Jeong is in our office now.

192
00:15:58,620 --> 00:16:00,220
With the return of 100,000 dollars,

193
00:16:00,520 --> 00:16:01,619
the company is considering...

194
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:03,660
ending the matter with your dismissal.

195
00:16:06,460 --> 00:16:08,700
I don't have it. I spent it all.

196
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:18,910
You used that as
settlement money, didn't you?

197
00:16:19,810 --> 00:16:20,810
Yes.

198
00:16:21,210 --> 00:16:22,780
Thanks to that, I was able to settle.

199
00:16:22,910 --> 00:16:23,940
So...

200
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:27,880
I'll just face the punishment.

201
00:16:32,420 --> 00:16:33,490
Bon Joo.

202
00:16:35,020 --> 00:16:36,090
Embezzling...

203
00:16:37,590 --> 00:16:39,760
under 100,000 dollars can result
in 4 to 16 months of imprisonment.

204
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:42,660
Embezzling between 100,000
dollars to 500,000 dollars...

205
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:46,630
can result in 1 year to
3 years of imprisonment.

206
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:50,700
Then I'll probably serve a year in prison.

207
00:16:52,340 --> 00:16:53,970
So I earned 100,000 dollars
in 1 year. That's not so bad.

208
00:16:55,110 --> 00:16:56,510
Is this about Moon Jin?

209
00:17:01,420 --> 00:17:03,180
Lawsuits are just unbearable.

210
00:17:03,780 --> 00:17:05,350
I'd rather serve a year in prison.

211
00:17:06,250 --> 00:17:08,560
("Golf Cart Tipped Over")
("Is Caddie Solely Responsible?")

212
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:19,800
Then we'll handle it as embezzlement.

213
00:17:27,340 --> 00:17:28,340
But I have a question.

214
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:30,680
Sure.

215
00:17:32,380 --> 00:17:34,680
If it's one million dollars,
how many years would it be?

216
00:17:38,690 --> 00:17:39,690
What?

217
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:42,890
Are you asking what
your sentence would be...

218
00:17:43,660 --> 00:17:45,130
if you embezzled one million dollars?

219
00:17:45,330 --> 00:17:46,330
Yes.

220
00:17:46,890 --> 00:17:47,960
Did you...

221
00:17:49,330 --> 00:17:50,500
embezzle a million dollars?

222
00:17:51,570 --> 00:17:53,570
No, not me.

223
00:18:15,420 --> 00:18:16,460
What's going on?

224
00:18:18,190 --> 00:18:19,260
Darn it.

225
00:18:33,770 --> 00:18:35,110
(Passport)

226
00:18:47,790 --> 00:18:48,860
What is this about?

227
00:18:49,220 --> 00:18:50,660
Could you spare us a moment?

228
00:18:51,760 --> 00:18:53,530
Well, I have to leave now...

229
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:57,060
for a business trip.
Let's talk another time.

230
00:18:58,370 --> 00:18:59,530
Are you going to the US?

231
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:04,100
Yes.

232
00:19:04,101 --> 00:19:06,410
To take over the flower delivery company.

233
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:08,480
Am I right?

234
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:22,960
My goodness.

235
00:19:24,460 --> 00:19:26,990
Excuse us. May we ask you some questions?

236
00:19:27,660 --> 00:19:31,770
Did you receive caddie training?

237
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:34,000
Caddie training? Yes, we
all completed the training.

238
00:19:34,030 --> 00:19:36,040
You have to complete
the training to work here.

239
00:19:36,570 --> 00:19:39,270
We heard you had to pay
for the training. Is it true?

240
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:40,940
Yes, a 300-dollar deposit.

241
00:19:41,210 --> 00:19:42,610
Pardon? A deposit?

242
00:19:43,310 --> 00:19:45,709
But why? Unless it was needed...

243
00:19:45,710 --> 00:19:48,579
to issue banknotes or...

244
00:19:48,580 --> 00:19:50,350
Why would caddies be
required to pay a deposit?

245
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:53,150
We heard they had to pay a deposit.

246
00:19:53,590 --> 00:19:54,660
The thing is,

247
00:19:56,990 --> 00:20:00,560
do you know how often the caddies quit?

248
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:05,000
Ninety percent of them quit as
soon as they complete their training.

249
00:20:05,730 --> 00:20:08,539
Then what about us? We fed them...

250
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:09,870
and even trained them.

251
00:20:10,300 --> 00:20:12,270
If they run away because
they can't work as caddies...

252
00:20:13,140 --> 00:20:15,840
The company has to take
care of all the expenses.

253
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:18,950
That's why they're all required
to pay a 300-dollar deposit.

254
00:20:19,150 --> 00:20:21,580
They get it all back when
they leave the company.

255
00:20:22,020 --> 00:20:23,050
So?

256
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:24,790
Did they get their money back?

257
00:20:25,490 --> 00:20:26,990
They say we'd get it all back, but...

258
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:29,659
How would you get it back
when you're running away?

259
00:20:29,660 --> 00:20:30,660
You'd sneak out in secret.

260
00:20:31,630 --> 00:20:34,089
We at least received
training, and they feed us too,

261
00:20:34,090 --> 00:20:35,130
so we can call it even.

262
00:20:35,430 --> 00:20:37,659
Hey, they won't give us the
money back even if we ask for it.

263
00:20:37,660 --> 00:20:39,370
I've never seen anyone
who got their deposit back.

264
00:20:40,270 --> 00:20:42,200
I heard you never had to
pay such a deposit in the past.

265
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:44,910
Then when did it start?

266
00:20:45,270 --> 00:20:48,040
It all began when that
cheapskate joined the company.

267
00:20:48,310 --> 00:20:49,380
Mr. Lee Hyeong Taek.

